<br>
The house wouldn't cheat - they don't have to.  They win by playing by the rules :) under no circumstances would they chance it, IMHO.<br>
<br>
Nobody playing $5 blackjack is ever gonna get booted for counting.  As long as you're not obvious about it (and don't use any sort of computer aide or take notes on paper or what have you) they'll leave you alone.  Card counters DO win - but not by a huge margin.  20% maybe - so if you play $300/hr and win $60/hr by skillful play - that's nothing to them.<br>
<br>
Real card counters (people who make a difference to the casino bottom line) generally work in teams and will have about a $100,000 bankroll when they walk into the casino.  The same 20% now will yield them $20-30,000/hour ... you can see why they rapidly get banned.<br>
<br>
I card count for &quot;sport&quot; and have never ever made money off of  it :) but it makes the game a bit more fun than just sitting there following basic strategy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utrindletrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trindle Trueheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pally Chick :)</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/1/01 5:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blackjack Problem</span><hr size=1> My Personal Blackjack rules.<br>
<br>
1.  Always assume the Dealer has a 10 Down.<br>
<br>
2.  Always split 8's and aces.<br>
<br>
3.  Always play the same way the house does.  <br>
Um.. they usually win, there's something to hitting on 16's or less.  I'm superstitious about 12's though... that damn number almost always burns me. <br>
I once heard the average dealer's hand is 18.93 or something like that.  Play to beat it.<br>
<br>
4.  Never play Blackjack in Tahoe.  Just don't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5.  Tip your dealer, Tip your dealer, Tip your dealer.  <br>
They <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> take care of you if you pay attention.<br>
<br>
6.  VERY IMPORTANT.  Starting off at a new table, If you lose more than 5 hands in a row, LEAVE and find another table.  Always hit a table with happy people, Never sit down at a table with quiet negative people.<br>
  <br>
<br>
Call it luck, call it sticking to the rules, i <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> usually</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> come away from a night of black Jack with chips to cash in. (profit)<br>
<br>
I love seeing nervous pit bosses *grin*<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucogito.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cogito</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord of the Whacky Woondarland</span><br>  Posts: 1281<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/1/01 9:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://voxton.hypermart.net/sigs/sig.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blackjack Problem</span><hr size=1> OK I shall critique this -- don't take it harshly please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
1. Always assume the Dealer has a 10 Down.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Don't assume that the dealer always has a 10 down. The dealer is only as likely to have a 10 down, as any other player on the table. But be aware of the fact that 10s are four times more likely to be the dealer's downcard -- and your downcard. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
2. Always split 8's and aces.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Agreed. Unless you are counting -- and are good at it, heheh. I never were. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
3. Always play the same way the house does. <br>
Um.. they usually win, there's something to hitting on 16's or less. I'm superstitious about 12's though... that damn number almost always burns me. <br>
I once heard the average dealer's hand is 18.93 or something like that. Play to beat it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> No! Don't play the same way the house does. The house has a huge advantage over you: they play last, and thus if the house, and the player busts, the house still wins. The advantage the player has, is that 21 is paid 1.5, rather than 1, for the player -- but not for the house. This means your strategy should be quite different from the house strategy. I don't know if the average dealer's hand is 18.93, as I never got into the number; the actual mathematics. It sounds quite intimidating, 18.93, but then again I do not know what a player's average hand is. <br>
</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
4. Never play Blackjack in Tahoe. Just don't.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I agree. Enjoy the scenery instead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
5. Tip your dealer, Tip your dealer, Tip your dealer. <br>
They will take care of you if you pay attention.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I agree. But make sure you make your tip in the form of a bet! I enjoy tipping, and tipping well. I never tipped a blackjack dealer except in the form of a bet. Sometimes, I made their tip as big as my bet. I don't think it influenced my wins, but well, I read yer average dealer were as much of a gambler, as yer average casino visitor, and having a bet on the table riding on you, makes you sorta feel like part of the action. I do wish tips went to dealers personally though, and not into some community box. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
6. VERY IMPORTANT. Starting off at a new table, If you lose more than 5 hands in a row, LEAVE and find another table. Always hit a table with happy people, Never sit down at a table with quiet negative people.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I do not believe that a dealer is hot or cold. There are no such things as streaks, except in retrospect. I believe I will do equally well, or badly, at a table where people are happy, or sad. Those are just cards, coming out of the shoe, people. Not divine karma. However, I do realize that this is a hobby, and not a job. So if you want to have fun, yes stay away. <br>
</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
